description.narrative:
As part of the project "Women and Sustainable Energies" a Financial Institution (Coris Bank International) was recruited to house the funds allocated to 12 cooperative societies in the form  of grants and loans in order to guarantee a good financial management and a better follow-up of the activities of unblocking funds.
In summurize, it consist to: 
 - Develop a participatory management guide for the credit fund and grants;
- Support the opening of accounts for the benefit of cooperative societies;
- Shelter / house the credit and subsidy funds of the twelve (12) Cooperative Societies in a financial institution;
- Supporting cooperative societies in the implementation of credit management tools;
- Make the contracts as well as the disbursements of the credit and subsidy fund for the benefit of the cooperative societies;
- Track the repayments of funds;
- Write monthly and periodic reports;
- Continue the sustainable management of the credit fund after the project;
The amount of contract is  915,578.17 €. This amount includes 669,935.25 € in form of grant, 223,311.75 € in form of loan and  22,331.17 € like MFI management costs.
